terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.10.27; 
only referred to as Hadoram (הֲדוֹרָם); 
son of Joktan; 
a brother of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, Uzal, Diklah, Obal, Abimael, Sheba, Ophir, Havilah and Jobab.

A man living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.20.24; 
referred to as Adoram (אֲדֹרָם), or Adoniram (אֲדֹנִירָם), or Hadoram (הֲדֹרָם); 
a son of Abda.

A man living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.8.10; 
referred to as Joram (יוֹרָם), or Hadoram (הֲדוֹרָם); 
a son of Toi.

An Edomite king living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.36.39; 
referred to as Hadad (הֲדַד), or Hadar (הֲדַר); 
husband of Mehetabel. § an Edomite king
